---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is AI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)"
  description="AI is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's a three-toed sloth from South America. Learn AI strategy and extensions."
  keywords="is ai a scrabble word, ai scrabble, ai valid scrabble, ai points scrabble, two letter words scrabble, ai meaning scrabble, three-toed sloth"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is AI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)",
    "description": "AI is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's a three-toed sloth from South America.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ai-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is AI a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, AI is valid in both the TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 2 points (A=1, I=1) and refers to a three-toed sloth native to South America." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does AI mean in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "In Scrabble, AI refers to a three-toed sloth (genus Bradypus) found in South America. It has nothing to do with artificial intelligence in this context — it's a zoological term that has been in dictionaries for centuries." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What words can you make from AI in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "AI extends into many words: AID (4pts), AIM (5pts), AIR (3pts), AIS (3pts plural), AIDE (5pts), AILS (4pts), AIMS (6pts), AIRS (4pts), AIRY (7pts). The S-hook (AIS) is particularly useful for parallel plays." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is AI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Yes, AI is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. Forget artificial intelligence — in Scrabble, AI refers to a three-toed sloth from South America. This tiny word packs tactical punch when you need to clear vowels or set up parallel plays.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Valid Both</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">AI</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · A=1, I=1 · A three-toed sloth (South America)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">AI is one of the most common two-letter words you'll encounter in competitive Scrabble. Its all-vowel composition makes it perfect for dumping excess vowels while maintaining board position.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">9 A-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">9 I-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Value: Vowel Management</h2>

      <p>AI is your go-to play when your rack is flooded with vowels. Here's why experienced players love it:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Vowel dump:</span> Holding AAIIO? Play AI to shed two vowels at once and draw consonants that unlock higher-scoring plays on your next turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays:</span> AI placed parallel to an existing word creates multiple crosswords. If WORD is on the board, placing AI below forms W+A and O+I simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Endgame finisher:</span> With limited board space in the endgame, AI fits into tight corners where longer words can't reach.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AI Extensions and Hooks</h2>

      <p>AI extends into dozens of common English words, making it a reliable setup play:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ 3-Letter Extensions</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">AID (4), AIM (5), AIR (3), AIS (3), AIT (3)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔗 4+ Letter Extensions</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">AIDE (5), AILS (4), AIMS (6), AIRS (4), AIRY (7), AIDS (5)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">With 9 A-tiles and 9 I-tiles in the bag, you'll hold both letters <span class="text-white font-medium">frequently throughout the game</span>. Knowing AI is valid means you always have a play available — no passing required, even with a vowel-heavy rack.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AI vs Other 2-Letter A Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">AI</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">2pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">AA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">AD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">AX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-li-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is LI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/is-oe-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is OE a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
